title: For Sale:  Daewoo DR-200 .223
postcontent:
Daewoo DR-200 .223 cal.
The Daewoo DR-200 is the civilian version of the Daewoo K2, the replacement rifle for the Colt M16, built in the Colt plant in South Korea. The DR-200 uses an AK-style long stroke gas piston and recoil spring, an FAL-style gas plug with three position gas adjustment, an AR-style bolt, and fixed ejector like the Stoner 63. The DR-200 has a unique rear sight that does both windage and elevation adjustment and a hooded tapered front sight post. The trigger group is similar to the AR with a crisp break and short reset. The overall balance of the rifle is quite good. The DR-200 uses AR15 magazines and takes down like a FN FAL, and with the precision manufacturing of an AR-15 has the dead nuts reliability of an AK. The DR-200 is both accurate (1 moa) and reliable and comes drilled and tapped for optics rails. This DR-200 was imported by Kimber of Oregon, is new and unfired, and in excellent condition having been stored in my gun safe for 32 years and cleaned/oiled regularly. Comes with 2 magazines. Daewoo K2 folding stock available. Price is $1200.00
